<subSubSection id="08D56EDBFFC4FFCF9BEFF0CF8769F8E6" box="[151,883,1775,1799]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="40703D50FFC4FFCF9BEFF0CF8769F8E6" blockId="4.[151,883,1775,1799]" box="[151,883,1775,1799]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC4FFCF9BEFF0CF8539F8E6" bold="true" box="[151,291,1775,1799]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">
<typeStatus id="9F7483F2FFC4FFCF9BEFF0CF84D6F8E6" box="[151,204,1775,1799]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC4FFCF9A52F0D086B3F8E6" authority="Endrodi, 1967" authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1967" box="[298,681,1775,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Cryptoryctes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peterseni">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC4FFCF9A52F0D0860AF8E6" box="[298,528,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Cryptoryctes peterseni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC4FFCF996EF0CF86B3F8E6" author="Endrodi, S." box="[534,681,1775,1799]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" pagination="301 - 307" refId="ref3968" refString="Endrodi, S. (1967) Die Dynastinen, Rutelinen und Hybosorinen der Noona Dan Expedition nach den Philippinen, Bismarck- und Salomon Inseln (Col. Scarabaeidae). Entomologiske Meddelelser, 15, 301 - 307." type="journal article" year="1967">Endrődi, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, hereby designated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08D56EDBFFC4FFCE9BEFF11586FCFE4F" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="140" pageId="4" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="40703D50FFC4FFCE9BEFF11586FCFE4F" blockId="4.[151,1437,1845,2016]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="140" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC4FFCF9BEFF1158563F8AE" bold="true" box="[151,377,1845,1871]" pageId="4" pageNumber="139">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Mentum strongly compressed and reflexed at ligula; mandibles exposed, margins simply curved, without teeth; maxillary palps with apical palpomere ovoid, not truncate. Antenna with 10 antennomeres; club with 3 antennomeres, rather broadly ovate and slightly shorter than all of shaft antennomeres combined. Clyp- eus vertical, concave, with anterior margin rounded, not shovel-shaped, without a carina immediately behind apex. Clypeofrontal suture obvious, concave either side of middle. Frons simple, without a horn, tubercle, or transverse carina. Pronotum with anterior margin membranous, apical horn forming the anterior margin and two lateral horns, all directed forwards and upwards near apices, area between lateral horns not depressed, upper surface smooth and shiny. Elytra without obvious punctation, surface shiny, striae indistinct. Propygidium without a stridulatory area, apical margin not produced backwards. Protibia with 3 teeth, basal tooth not as prominent as middle tooth and more rounded, spur inserted posterior to base of medial denticle; metatibiae short, strongly dilated towards apex. Param- eres simple, lateral margins linear and tapering to apex, extreme apices curved outwards, face sublinear in lateral view, phallobase length: paramere length approximately 1.2:1 (the illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9F41F74F80C5FE68" author="Endrodi, S." box="[1081,1247,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" pagination="301 - 307" refId="ref3968" refString="Endrodi, S. (1967) Die Dynastinen, Rutelinen und Hybosorinen der Noona Dan Expedition nach den Philippinen, Bismarck- und Salomon Inseln (Col. Scarabaeidae). Entomologiske Meddelelser, 15, 301 - 307." type="journal article" year="1967">Endrődi (1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9F93F74F813FFE68" author="Endrodi, S." box="[1259,1317,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" pagination="243 - 320" refId="ref4008" refString="Endrodi, S. (1971) Monographie der Dynastinae 4. Tribus Pentodontini (papuanische und pazifische Inselwelt (Coleoptera: Lamellicornia: Melolonthidae). Pacific Insects, 13, 243 - 320." type="journal article" year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9E49F74E8170FE68" author="Endrodi, S." box="[1329,1386,366,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" refId="ref4044" refString="Endrodi, S. (1985) The Dynastinae of the World. Junk, Dordrecht, Netherlands, 800 pp." type="book" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
) are somewhat distorted and do not show the same ratio).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08D56EDBFFC5FFCE9BBFF796800FFCF4" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="40703D50FFC5FFCE9BBFF796868AFD80" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9BBFF7968558FE31" bold="true" box="[199,322,438,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of dilated metatibiae, shape of the clypeus and pygidium, simply curved man- dibles, absence of a frontal horn, tubercle or carina, and three pronotal horns in 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9F62F7FB8066FE14" authorityName="Allsopp &amp; Hutchinson" authorityYear="2020" box="[1050,1148,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Niuailan" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9F62F7FB8066FE14" box="[1050,1148,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Niuailan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allow clear identification from other New Guinean species in 
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9953F7DF86F3FDF8" author="Endrodi, S." box="[555,745,510,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" refId="ref4044" refString="Endrodi, S. (1985) The Dynastinae of the World. Junk, Dordrecht, Netherlands, 800 pp." type="book" year="1985">Endrődi’s (1985)</bibRefCitation>
key to 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9844F7DF87D1FDF8" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1842" box="[828,971,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pentodontini">Pentodontini</taxonomicName>
of the Oriental and Papuan regions albeit with the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9AFAF4038684FDDC" authority="Dechambre, 1998" authorityName="Dechambre" authorityYear="1998" box="[386,670,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Siralus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9AFAF40385CBFDDC" box="[386,465,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Siralus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9AA0F4038684FDDC" author="Dechambre, R. - P." box="[472,670,547,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" pagination="29 - 34" refId="ref3900" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. (1998) Siralus insularis, nouveau genre, nouvelle espece de Pentodontini de Nouvelle-Guinee (Coleoptera, Dynastidae). Coleopteres, 4, 29 - 34." type="journal article" year="1998">Dechambre, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and the recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE98E7F40380ACFDDC" authority="Endrodi, 1963" authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1963" box="[927,1206,547,573]" genus="Clysterius" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE98E7F403800BFDDC" box="[927,1041,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Clysterius</emphasis>
Endrődi, 1963
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9BCEF46785B5FD80" authority="Arrow, 1914" authorityName="Arrow" authorityYear="1914" box="[182,431,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Papuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9BCEF4678501FD81" box="[182,283,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Papuana</emphasis>
Arrow, 1914
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="245E40A1FFC5FFCE9AC5F4678699FD80" author="Dechambre, R. - P." box="[445,643,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" pagination="29 - 34" refId="ref3900" refString="Dechambre, R. - P. (1998) Siralus insularis, nouveau genre, nouvelle espece de Pentodontini de Nouvelle-Guinee (Coleoptera, Dynastidae). Coleopteres, 4, 29 - 34." type="journal article" year="1998">Dechambre 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40703D50FFC5FFCE9BBFF44B800FFCF4" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">
From species of 
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9AFBF44B86ABFD65" box="[387,689,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9AFBF44B8607FD64" authorityName="Ozdikmen" authorityYear="2009" box="[387,541,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Carneoryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carneoryctes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="87CF46D3FFC5FFCE9951F44B86ABFD65" authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1967" box="[553,689,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Cryptoryctes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peterseni">N. peterseni</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
differs in its almost smooth pronotal and elytral surfaces, absence of a pronotal depression, discal sculpturing or setae, elytral surfaces almost smooth, striae restricted to extreme base, antennal club slightly shorter than shaft, basal tooth of protibia smaller and more rounded than middle tooth, metatibial spurs straight and of about equal length, parameres that curve out and not inwards at the apices, and the phallobase of the aedeagus much shorter relative to the length of the parameres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08D56EDBFFC5FFCE9BBFF53F8180FCD8" box="[199,1434,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="40703D50FFC5FFCE9BBFF53F8180FCD8" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" box="[199,1434,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis id="72BBE142FFC5FFCE9BBFF53F8554FCD8" bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the island of the 
<typeStatus id="9F7483F2FFC5FFCE99F7F53F86A5FCD8" box="[655,703,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="140">type</typeStatus>
locality—Niu Ailan in Tok Pisin. It is to be treated as masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
